{"info": {"author": "Hugo Herter", "author_email": "git@hugoherter.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "Operating System :: POSIX :: Linux", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "description": "Reloadr\n=======\n\nPython hot code reloading tool.\n\n``pip install reloadr``\n\nUsage\n=====\n\nYou can simply decorate your functions / classes with ``@autoreload`` and\nyou are ready to go.\n\n.. code:: python\n\n    from reloadr import autoreload\n\n    @autoreload\n    def do_something(a, b):\n        return a + b\n\n    @autoreload\n    class SomeThing:\n        def do_stuff(self):\n            pass\n\nAdvanced usage\n==============\n\nTo reload the code manually, you can use of the following:\n\n.. code:: Python\n\n    from reloadr import reloadr\n\n    @reloadr\n    class SomeThing:\n        def do_stuff(self):\n            pass\n\n    # Manual reload\n    SomeThing._reload()\n\n    # Automatic reload using filesystem notifications\n    SomeThing._start_watch_reload()\n\n    # Automatic reload in a thread every 1 second\n    SomeThing._start_timer_reload(1)\n\nExamples\n========\n\nLaunch an example (they each contain an infinite loop), then change the\nsource code of the decorated class or function.\n\n``git clone https://github.com/hoh/reloadr.git``\n\n``python examples/01_manual_reload.py``\n\nHow it works\n============\n\nInstead of importing your source file again, which can lead to undesired side\neffects, Reloadr fetches the new code of your function within the Python source\nfile, and executes that code in the environment of your already loaded module.\n\nThis allows it to reload code that is followed by blocking instructions such\nas the infinite loops you can find in the examples.\n\nTo achieve this, Reloadr relies on  `RedBaron\n<https://github.com/psycojoker/redbaron/>`_ , an great tool for manipulating\nPython source code.\n\nFuture plans\n============\n\nThis project is still in its early stages. All ideas for improvement are welcome.\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/hoh/reloadr", "keywords": "reload hot code reloading", "license": "LGPLv3", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "Reloadr", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/Reloadr/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/Reloadr/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/hoh/reloadr"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/Reloadr/0.4.1/", "requires_dist": ["watchdog"], "requires_python": "", "summary": "Hot code reloading tool for Python", "version": "0.4.1", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <div id=\"reloadr\">\n<h2>Reloadr</h2>\n<p>Python hot code reloading tool.</p>\n<p><tt>pip install reloadr</tt></p>\n</div>\n<div id=\"usage\">\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<p>You can simply decorate your functions / classes with <tt>@autoreload</tt> and\nyou are ready to go.</p>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">reloadr</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">autoreload</span>\n\n<span class=\"nd\">@autoreload</span>\n<span class=\"k\">def</span> <span class=\"nf\">do_something</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"p\">):</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">return</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"o\">+</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span>\n\n<span class=\"nd\">@autoreload</span>\n<span class=\"k\">class</span> <span class=\"nc\">SomeThing</span><span class=\"p\">:</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">def</span> <span class=\"nf\">do_stuff</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">):</span>\n        <span class=\"k\">pass</span>\n</pre>\n</div>\n<div id=\"advanced-usage\">\n<h2>Advanced usage</h2>\n<p>To reload the code manually, you can use of the following:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">reloadr</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">reloadr</span>\n\n<span class=\"nd\">@reloadr</span>\n<span class=\"k\">class</span> <span class=\"nc\">SomeThing</span><span class=\"p\">:</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">def</span> <span class=\"nf\">do_stuff</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">):</span>\n        <span class=\"k\">pass</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># Manual reload</span>\n<span class=\"n\">SomeThing</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">_reload</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># Automatic reload using filesystem notifications</span>\n<span class=\"n\">SomeThing</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">_start_watch_reload</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># Automatic reload in a thread every 1 second</span>\n<span class=\"n\">SomeThing</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">_start_timer_reload</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n</div>\n<div id=\"examples\">\n<h2>Examples</h2>\n<p>Launch an example (they each contain an infinite loop), then change the\nsource code of the decorated class or function.</p>\n<p><tt>git clone <span class=\"pre\">https://github.com/hoh/reloadr.git</span></tt></p>\n<p><tt>python examples/01_manual_reload.py</tt></p>\n</div>\n<div id=\"how-it-works\">\n<h2>How it works</h2>\n<p>Instead of importing your source file again, which can lead to undesired side\neffects, Reloadr fetches the new code of your function within the Python source\nfile, and executes that code in the environment of your already loaded module.</p>\n<p>This allows it to reload code that is followed by blocking instructions such\nas the infinite loops you can find in the examples.</p>\n<p>To achieve this, Reloadr relies on  <a href=\"https://github.com/psycojoker/redbaron/\" rel=\"nofollow\">RedBaron</a> , an great tool for manipulating\nPython source code.</p>\n</div>\n<div id=\"future-plans\">\n<h2>Future plans</h2>\n<p>This project is still in its early stages. All ideas for improvement are welcome.</p>\n</div>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6544149, "releases": {"0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "63c9f994331b8b2b75dbd074575f18ef", "sha256": "cee67e101f363e5cb2e1270b1013a266093e4546fe31142265533c81dc644a75"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "Reloadr-0.1.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "63c9f994331b8b2b75dbd074575f18ef", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 2063, "upload_time": "2015-12-17T19:17:10", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2015-12-17T19:17:10.566754Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/c7/d6/e38f856895d8b993ede7fac4544dbfac6c5d5c9638d9d2f5a6cd42db7864/Reloadr-0.1.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.1.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "5ff061219122e4dbb59665af779634df", "sha256": "42d61fa4d9b32b709b240118553a35bd803dce56403a9e2385e9214f93c2504c"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "Reloadr-0.1.1.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "5ff061219122e4dbb59665af779634df", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 2182, "upload_time": "2015-12-17T19:20:42", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2015-12-17T19:20:42.009346Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/52/6a/9a020aaa04746520aa469879b708cf708b863818ee408a4cbe96bb8452bf/Reloadr-0.1.1.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.1.2": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "ec8184995be7eea9b89cda1f797294f7", "sha256": "7cedd5f7f7ff273633964237bf83cd91cf4f91256d9615d485d53ac9401cfd95"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "Reloadr-0.1.2.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "ec8184995be7eea9b89cda1f797294f7", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 2741, "upload_time": "2016-10-13T11:52:00", "upload_ti